/*
============================================================================
FINAL KEYWORD – INTERVIEW REVISION
Author: Om
============================================================================

final means constant value.

Once assigned it cannot be changed.

Example:

final int x = 4;

x = 10  ❌ ERROR

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

final with variables

final int x = 4;

Value cannot be modified.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

final with methods

Method cannot be overridden.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

final with class

Class cannot be inherited.

Example:

final class A {}

class B extends A ❌ ERROR

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Example from code:

static final double PI;

static{
    PI = 3.14;
}

Here:

PI becomes constant for entire program.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

INTERVIEW POINT

final + static is commonly used for constants.

Example:

static final double PI = 3.14;

============================================================================
*/